    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style of Mannerism found in the visual arts north of the Alps in the 16th and early 17th centuries. Northern Mannerism in the early sixteenth century is characterized by thematic traits that derive from late Gothic art. Many of the early sixteenth-century Mannerists were based in Antwerp, with other centers in France, Germany, and the southern and northern Netherlands.</Note_Text>
